To use CAPS2 patched, you can just get the vCAPS-static, rename it to
vCAPS and place it in your $PATH.

The statically linked binary was built on CRUX 3.6.1 (https://crux.nu/),
as follows:

unzip caps2_src.zip
cd caps2.0_src
cp -a lib/ caps2.0_src
cp Makefile.static caps2.0_src
cd caps2.0_src
patch -p1 -i ../01_caps_verbose.patch
make -f Makefile.static

Compiler flags used: "-O2 -fPIC -march=x86-64", in our experience -O3
did not yield any significant performance improvement. Static libraries
build on the same system:

libbpp-numcalc.a (1.8.0): Bio++ 1.9 NumCalc Library
libbpp-phyl.a (1.9.0) Bio++ 1.9 Phyl Library
libbpp-seq.a (1.7.0) Bio++ 1.9 Seq Library
libbpp-utils.a (1.5.0) Bio++ 1.9 Utils Library
libc.a (2.32) The C library used in the GNU system
libgsl.a (2.7.1) A numerical library for C and C++ programmers
libgslcblas.a (2.7.1) A numerical library for C and C++ programmers
libm.a (2.32) The C library used in the GNU system
libstdc++.a (10.3.0) The GNU Compiler Collection
